<h2 id="goals">Goals</h2>

<p>This basic Physics course has three main goals:</p>
<ul>
  <li>By the end of this course you will be able to look at the world around you and start describing it in a formal (mathematical) language.</li>
  <li>By the end of this course you will be able to read a graph and tell the story behind it, i.e., you will translate a formal (mathematical) language into regular speech any human can understand.</li>
  <li>We will get acquainted with the concept of Energy. This, in my humblest opinion, is one of the most important ideas in Science.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="patron-saint">Patron saint</h2>

<p>Galileo is undoubtedly our hero in this course. Honorable runners-up: Archimedes and Newton.</p>

<p><img src="/archive/physics/gifs/Galileo-quote.png" alt="" /></p>

